      • getDateSent

        public static java.lang.String getDateSent(javax.mail.Message m)
                                    throws javax.mail.MessagingException
        Parameters:
        m - the message whose sent date will be returned
        Returns:
        the sent date of the message.
        • If it was sent in the past 24 hours, then return in the format hh:mm
        • Otherwise, if it was sent in the past week, then return in the format "xxx dd/mm", where xxx is the abbreviated name of the day, e.g. Sun 08/11
        • Otherwise return in the format dd/mm/yyyy
        Throws:
        javax.mail.MessagingException

      • toggleSeen

        public static void toggleSeen(javax.mail.Message m)
                       throws javax.mail.MessagingException
